                    h3 Banking company website
                    p.text-justify First I developed a simple
                      strong
                        em  gamified
                      |  website for a banking company - using Materialize.css and a small MySql database -
                      | to help costumers to find some resources.
                      | I then deployed it in production under a Node.js server.
                      br
                      | The website is currently tested on 10.000 people.
                      br
                    a.btn.btn-primary.btn-lg.complementary-text(href="http://natixisinterepargne-silvousplay.symetrix.fr/" target="_blank") View my work
              .panel.panel-default
                #snfx-big-one.panel-heading(role='tab')
                  h4.panel-title
                    a.collapsed(role='button', data-toggle='collapse', data-parent='#accordion', href='#snfx-collapse-two', aria-expanded='false', aria-controls='snfx-collapse-two')
                      | The main one
                #snfx-collapse-two.panel-collapse.collapse(role='tabpanel', aria-labelledby='snfx-big-one')
                  .panel-body
                    h3 Management platform
                    p.text-justify My biggest task was to develop the&nbsp;
                      abbr.initialism(title="Proof of Concept") POC
                      |  of an
                      strong  extremely modular
                      |  web platform, dedicated to team management.
                      | I had to integrate several
                      strong  third party web services (using REST APIs)
                      |  such as LinkedIn, Moodle, YouTube and an Elastic Search server.
                      | I used Angular2 (beta) framework for the front-side
                      | as well as a MySQL server and a Node.JS server as backend,
                      | and deployed it.
                    p.text-justify I also had the occasion to
                      strong  configure and deploy a CAS server
                      |  by myself - although supported by the network administrator -
                      | which is something i'm really proud about.
                    p.text-justify Unfortunately, this is a private work of the company I worked for,
                      |  so I can not provide the source code nor a screenshot of the result.
